9. MVC Architecture
Model
World state — all NPC states, suspicion meter, soul count, time of day
NPC data — personality profiles, hidden desires, current state, conversation history
Deal system — active deals, ripple effect queue, soul value tracking
Investigator logic — patrol state, interview targets, suspicion thresholds
AI service — sends prompts to Claude API, parses JSON, updates NPC state

View
Overworld renderer — tile map, NPC sprites, player, day/night lighting overlay
Encounter renderer — NPC portrait, dialogue box, mood visuals, hellish vignette effect
UI overlay — soul counter, suspicion meter, time of day, deal history log
Transition handler — manages cut and fade between overworld and encounter view

Controller
Player input — movement in overworld, free text input in encounter view
Trigger handler — detects door/spawn/region overlaps and fires events
Encounter controller — manages conversation turns, calls AI service, applies response to model
Game loop — tick-based updates for NPC routines, investigator patrol, suspicion changes


